<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: #5b5a5a; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin">Thanks for choosing the CITGO fleet card program. Ensure your account stays secure with our four security tips. </SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: black; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin"><BR></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: #5a5b5b; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin"><BR>1. Remind drivers that if an attendant swipes the card in the card reader, they should keep it in their sight and make sure the same card is returned to them.</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: black; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin"> </SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: #5a5b5b; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin"><BR><BR>2. Always review your reports or better yet, check transaction details at </SPAN><A title="Check your account online" href="https://www.wextools.com/distrib/?source=citgo"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: #276d91; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin">CITGO Fleet Online</SPAN></A><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: #5a5b5b; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin"> to watch for discrepancies or unusual purchase patterns.<BR><BR>3. Control access to your account by notifying us of changes to the authorized fleet contact(s).<BR><BR>4. When a vehicle will be out of use for a period of time, collect the card to keep it secure. If a vehicle is sold or retired, immediately cancel and destroy the assigned card.</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: black; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin"><BR></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 16pt; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 9.0pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin"><BR></SPAN><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; COLOR: #5a5b5b; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-size: 7.5pt; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin">We're here for you 24/7, so be sure to give us call at 1-866-926-5615 if you have any questions. Thanks again, and welcome to the CITGO fleet card Program!<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>
